>
  <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.docs_hero
    eyebrow="Technical · Smart contracts"
    title="Blockster Bankroll — full reference."
    description="The Anchor program backing every bet and every pool. Every instruction, every account, every PDA seed, every error code. Built to be read end-to-end by auditors and integrators."
  />

  <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.page_toc items={[
    %{id: "overview", label: "Program overview"},
    %{id: "authority", label: "Authority model"},
    %{id: "pdas", label: "PDAs and seeds"},
    %{id: "accounts", label: "Account structures"},
    %{id: "constants", label: "Constants"},
    %{id: "instructions", label: "Instructions"},
    %{id: "errors", label: "Error codes"},
    %{id: "events", label: "Events"},
    %{id: "pause", label: "Pause behaviour"},
    %{id: "upgrade", label: "Upgrade authority"}
  ]} />

  <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.section id="overview" title="Program overview" eyebrow="01">
    <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.kv_table
      title="Identity"
      rows={[
        {"Program ID", "49up2uzZANpjTC3sgggbZazdHBii2vY9mVK3vk5dT2tm"},
        {"Cluster", if(BlocksterV2Web.Solscan.mainnet?(), do: "mainnet", else: "devnet (mainnet launch pending)")},
        {"Framework", "Anchor 0.30+ (Rust)"},
        {"Crate", "contracts/blockster-bankroll/programs/blockster-bankroll"},
        {"Settler service", "contracts/blockster-settler (Node/TypeScript)"},
        {"IDL", "contracts/blockster-bankroll/target/idl/blockster_bankroll.json"},
        {"Number of instructions", "22"},
        {"Number of account structs", "7"},
        {"Number of error codes", "32"},
        {"Number of emitted events", "14"}
      ]}
    />

    <p>
      The program is a single crate — no cross-program call chains that aren't standard CPIs (System, SPL Token, Metaplex Token Metadata). It holds two vaults (SOL + BUX), mints two LP tokens (SOL-LP + BUX-LP), registers up to 10 games with parametric multipliers, implements a commit-reveal settlement scheme, and supports a two-tier referral programme.
    </p>
  </BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.section>

  <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.section id="authority" title="Authority model" eyebrow="02">
    <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.kv_table
      title="Roles"
      rows={[
        {"authority", "Set once at initialize_registry, never changeable on-chain. Registers games, updates per-game config, toggles the global pause flag, creates LP metadata."},
        {"settler", "Submits commitments, settles bets, pays the PDA rent for BetOrder accounts. Rotated via update_config."},
        {"upgrade_authority", "Standard Solana upgrade authority on the program loader. Held off-chain, not referenced in program code."},
        {"player", "Signs deposits, withdrawals, reclaims. No persistent privilege; the sender of each instruction."}
      ]}
    />

    <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.callout kind="warning" title="authority is immutable on-chain">
      <p>
        The <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code>authority</BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code> field of <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code>GameRegistry</BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code> is set by <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code>initialize_registry</BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.inline_code> and has no instruction that rotates it. If that key is compromised, rotation requires redeploying the program via the upgrade authority. We document this explicitly as a <.link navigate={~p"/docs/security-audit"}>Medium-severity audit finding</.link> with a known remediation path.
      </p>
    </BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.callout>
  </BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.section>

  <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.section id="pdas" title="PDAs and seeds" eyebrow="03">
    <BlocksterV2Web.DocsComponents.spec_table
      cols={[
        %{key: :name, label: "PDA"},
        %{key: :seeds, label: "Seeds", mono: true},
